Might this share class from a producer's perspective being marketed to eligible counterparties?

Under MiFID regulation Article 30 paragraph 2 (http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legalcontent/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:32014L0065&from=EN) an eligible counterpart is one of the following:
(a) Investment firms;
(b) Credit institutions;
(c) Insurance companies;
(d) UCITs and their management companies;
(e) Pension funds and their management companies;
(f) other financial institutions authorised or regulated under Union law;
(g) national governments including public bodies dealing with public debt at
national level;
(h) central banks and supranational organisations.

