Does the share class charge a trail commission? If so, please provide this field with "yes".

A trail commission is a fee paid by the investor to a financial advisor each year that the investor owns an investment. This fee represents an incentive for the advisor to review a client's holdings and provide advice. Such a fee is usually expressed in a percentage of the total investment into a fund per year.

